<p>Design gives you the opportunity to put things into the world.</p>

<p>You get to help others every day.</p>

<p>By exploring new ideas and testing them.</p>

<p>You can start small and expand</p>

<p>and leave lasting impact.</p>

<p><strong>Make something and learn as you go.</strong></p>

<p>It gives you the opportunity to try something and see how people respond.</p>

<ol>
  <li>What can you create in a day that you can expand on?</li>
  <li>Will it be useful to you and others on your team, organization or at your company?</li>
  <li>Make your own hack day and share what you did with others on your team.</li>
  <li>Feedback is essential!</li>
  <li>You have the power to expand your skills, be helpful and never stop learning.</li>
  <li>You can practice solving design problems and getting feedback within your company.</li>
  <li>You will discover something new.</li>
</ol>

<p>And start to open your eyes to the needs of others.</p>
